LzNJLEIo4gh-X_rmDkNkNg
This is an awesome spot and honestly a go-to for me and most of my friends. The beer is always solid (ask for the Bourbon-Barrel-Aged Kiltlifter, never advertised, offered rarely, but incredibly worth it) and the food is a cut above typical bar food. For real, apples to oranges kind of comparison. Only downfalls, parking can be a problem and the place is hopping almost any day of the week so if you've got a group of 4 or more it can be tricky getting a spot together right away. Staff is decent too. They usually have the menu and beers down like pro's but with a busy spot like this if you're in a rush and need constant attention this might not be the place for you.

